Chargers Make Eric Weddle Highest-Paid Safety in History, NFL.Com Says

-- B y   L a r r y   S i d d o n s
-- 
2011-07-27T18:56:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/chargers-make-eric-weddle-highest-paid-safety-in-history-nfl-com-says.html
Eric Weddle became the highest-paid
safety in National Football League history when he agreed with
the San Diego Chargers on a five-year, $40 million contract,
NFL.com said.  Weddle re-signed with the Chargers in a deal that includes
$19 million guaranteed money and a $13 million signing bonus,
the website said, citing an unidentified person in the league.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  